  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Although morbidly obese subjects have larger than regular caloric intake, there is evidence
      that they suffer from nutritional deficiencies at a higher rate than the general population,
      probably because they eat mostly &quot;unhealthy food.&quot;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
